  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of national and international regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here's an overview:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislative Components\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n- Customer due diligence procedures\n\n3. Key Legislation by Country\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- United Kingdom: Proceeds of Crime Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must implement monitoring systems\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain detailed transaction records\n- Conduct customer risk assessments\n\n5. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory bodies\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\nThe framework aims to prevent financial crimes and track potentially illicit financial flows.",
